      "content": "idk i just feel like the way it's framed makes it sound like gas is always the bad guy and wind is the hero. if we're being real, if the lifecycle of wind has all these massive ecological costs from mining, isnt it also a bit of an environmental problem? why is one considered \"clean\" and the other just \"high-carbon\" when they both have huge impacts?",
